						<summary>

						<p>This inscription records a donation of two door jambs (<hi rend="italic">tirunilaikkāl</hi>) to the central shrine of the Chittiramēḻi-viṇṇagar <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Ādikēsavap-perumāḷ temple at Paruttippaḷḷi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Rājasiṅgach-chaturvēdimaṅgalam by Silambāṇḍai, son of Kaṇṇandai Siṟiyāṇḍai, of Kachchippaḷḷi for the merit of his uncle (<hi rend="italic">māmaṉ</hi>) Sempōttar Piḷḷaiyāṇḍai.</p>						

						</summary>
